curam.util.persistence.validation.customizable

Interface ValidationContext


  • public interface ValidationContext
    A ValidationContext represents a customizable validation.

    That is, each customizable validation has a corresponding ValidationContext. These are obtained from a ValidationContextFactory.

    See Also:
    ValidationContextFactory

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getValidationName()
      Return the fully scoped name of this validation.

    • Method Detail

      • getValidationName

        java.lang.String getValidationName()
        Return the fully scoped name of this validation.

        The name is of form fullyScopedValidatorInterfaceName.validationMethodName.

        Example: curam.sample.PersonCustomizableValidator. validateFirstName where curam.sample.PersonCustomizableValidator is the fully scoped validation interface name (i.e. including package) and validateFirstName is the validation method name.

        Returns:
        The fully scoped name of this validation.
